File: Eskom warned on Sunday that load-shedding could be implemented. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom warned on Sunday that load-shedding could be implemented. The power utility said the result of breakdowns at its plant made the system on vulnerable, therefore “the probability of load-shedding remains, but will only be implemented if absolutely necessary.” LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you Eskom said its emergency team is monitoring the system. However, it cautioned that unplanned breakdowns could result in load-shedding at short notice.